11/08/2003
ISTANBUL, Turkey -- Thousands of dignitaries, including Italian Prime Minister Silvio Berlusconi, Albanian Prime Minister Fatos Nano, and Turkish Foreign Minister Abdullah Gul, attended the wedding of Prime Minister Recep Tayyip Erdogan's son in Istanbul on Sunday (10 August). Bilal Erdogan, 22, and Reyyan Uzuner, 17, are expected to leave for the United States shortly. Bilal is a student at Harvard University and his bride is expected to complete high school in Boston. In his speech celebrating the marriage, Berlusconi said he would continue to work for Turkey's marriage with the EU. Italy currently holds the rotating EU presidency. (Hurriyet, Milliyet, Radikal - 11/08/03; AP, Reuters, AFP, Anadolu Agency, NTV, TRT 2, - 10/08/03)
